WITH the debate on the ANC succession issue heating up, senior leaders opposed to Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa s election as the next president reportedly explained their stance at Empangeni where the ANC in KZN held its provincial general council this weekend.According to sources at a commission chaired by Sihle Zikalala, the chairperson of the ANC in KwaZulu-Natal, said Ramaphosa s closeness to big business was likely to see him bowing to their often anti-poor agenda.The Marikana cloud hanging over Ramaphosa was a big political turn-off for others.SIHLE MAVUSO sihlem@thenewage.co.za